= Benjamin Wade

Benjamin Wade of Ohio is one of the most combative figures in the Republican Party. His blunt, unpolished manner conceals a razor-sharp political mind.

- @wade_ohio_machine: Mobilize the Ohio Machine
- @wade_worker_outreach: Reach Out to Workers
- @root: Return to main

@wade_ohio_machine
title: Mobilize the Ohio Machine
subtitle: Campaign in Ohio
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; OH_workers_rep += 4; OH_immigrant_laborers_rep += 3; OH_middle_class_rep += 1; OH_rural_rep -= 2

Wade's network of loyal Ohio Republicans springs into action. Ward bosses, veterans' lodges, and union halls all receive the word. Ohio, always competitive, swings a few degrees toward us.

@wade_worker_outreach
title: Reach Out to Workers
subtitle: Wade's blunt working-class style resonates with Northern labor.
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; workers_rep += 5; immigrant_laborers_rep += 3;

Wade speaks the language of working men: unvarnished, direct, and angry on their behalf. His tour of Northern factories and labor halls draws crowds and reminds workers that the Republican Party was built on free labor principles.

